# Powers of 3, 3^0 .. 3^4, each printed as a balanced ternary trit string
# on its own line.  Showcases the `*` op (multiply by 3): one instruction
# per power in btf, vs ~6 chars + value-many loop iterations in plain BF.
#
# Tape: cell0 = current power, cell1 = newline char (ASCII 10).
#
# Expected output:
#   +
#   +0
#   +00
#   +000
#   +0000

# cell1 = 10 (newline)
> ++++++++++ <

# 3^0 = 1
+ : > . <

# 3^1 = 3
* : > . <

# 3^2 = 9
* : > . <

# 3^3 = 27
* : > . <

# 3^4 = 81
* : > . <
